{"word":"H3518 - כָּבָה - kâbâh - kaw-baw' - Go out","slug":"H3518","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּבָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâbâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-baw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Go out"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D1;&#x05D4; - ka&#x0302;ba&#x0302;h</b> - <i>kaw-baw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>expire</i> or (causatively) to <i>extinguish</i> (fire, light, anger): - go (put) out, quench."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3521\">H3521</a>"}]}